{
  "stem": "27507.9",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But even if you looked like an Aryan, I think that one was-- it was said that people were-- Jews were recognized by their eyes, because the eyes were-- because they had those frightened eyes.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sorry?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And frightened expression.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Anyway, eyes, like animals that were being-- that were being hunted, practically.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they, suddenly-- suddenly, there were teenagers who appeared next to us, and started screaming [POLISH], a little Jewess, because I was so covered.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They covered-- they wrapped me up in some clothes so that I think I looked-- they mistook me, apart from anything else, for a girl, because I was wrapped up in some cloak, of some coat.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they mistook me for a girl.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they put something on my head, because it was cold.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my mother put-- probably wrapped up my head.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they thought it was a Jewish girl.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Anyway, we managed to throw them off, somehow.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we couldn't stay in Jula's place, because it was too dangerous.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we managed to change into another flat.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we changed the flats later on very regularly.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We changed them, and we changed them, because every time there was-- because living-- it was difficult to find a place to live.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then after, if you found a place to live, after a few weeks, something was happening.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Either the flat owner decided that we were not-- not quite kosher, you know?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That we were not proper Poles, as one should be.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But there was something funny about us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Or that there was suddenly danger of a blackmail.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we first-- I think after Jula, we first moved to the [POLISH], to the castle square, which is in the very center of the old town of Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
